> Setup and Configuration:

    git config --global user.name "your name"
    git config --global user.email "your name"
    git config --list ---> check config

> Repository Initialization:

    git init --> create new repo
    git clone repo_url --> copy existing repo

> File tracking:

    git status --> check file status
    git add --> add specific file
    git add. --> add all files

> Commit changes:

    git commit -m 'message' --> save changes
    git commit -am 'message' --> add + commit (tracked files only)

> Branching:

    git branch --> list branches
    git branch <name> --> create branch
    git checkout <branch> --> switch branch
    git checkout -b <branch> --> create + switch
    git switch <branch> --> modern way to switch

> Merging:

    git merge <branch> --> merge into current branch

> Remote repository:

    git remote add origin <url>
    git remote -v --> check remote

> Push and Pull:

    git push origin <branch> --> upload code
    git pull origin <branch> --> fetch + merge
    git fetch --> get latest changes (no merge)

> Undo changes:

    git restore <file> --> undo changes
    git reset <file> --> unstage file
    git reset --hard --> remove all local changes
    git revert <commit> --> undo commit safely

> Logs and History:

    git log --> full history
    git log --oneline --> short view

> Stashing (temporary save):
    git stash --> save changes temporarily
    git stash pop --> restore changes


















